  "kind": "Lemma",
  "title": "Convex hull as the smallest convex set",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let \\(P\\subseteq\\mathbb{R}^2\\). Then \\(\\conv(P)\\) is convex, contains \\(P\\), and\nis contained in every convex set that contains \\(P\\). Hence\n\\[\n \\conv(P)\n =\n \\bigcap\\{K\\subseteq\\mathbb{R}^2 : K\\text{ is convex and }P\\subseteq K\\}.\n\\]",
